##Installation Guide

Want to run the Campus Lost & Found Portal on your own laptop? 
Just follow these simple steps.

What You Need First

Git installed on your computer — download here
VS Code (or any code editor you like)
The Live Server extension for VS Code
A free Google account (to create a Firebase project)

That's it. No Node.js, no npm, no complicated setup — this project is built with plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Step 1: Get the Code on Your Computer

Open a terminal and type:
bashgit clone https://github.com/Anshratta/LOSTandFoundportal.git
cd LOSTandFoundportal
This copies the project to your computer and takes you inside the project folder.

Step 2: Create Your Own Firebase Project

Our site uses Firebase to store all the lost and found reports. You'll need to make your own Firebase project (it's free):

Go to Firebase Console
Click "Add Project" and name it anything you like
Click the Web icon (</>) to add a web app to your project
Firebase will show you a small code block called firebaseConfig — copy it
On the left menu, go to Build → Firestore Database → Create Database
When asked, choose Start in test mode


Step 3: Connect Firebase to the Project

Open the file called firebase.js in the project folder. Replace the existing config with the one you just copied from your own Firebase project, then save the file.
jsconst firebaseConfig = {
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    authDomain: "YOUR_PROJECT.firebaseapp.com",
    projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
    storageBucket: "YOUR_PROJECT.firebasestorage.app",
    messagingSenderId: "YOUR_SENDER_ID",
    appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};
This one small step connects your local copy of the project to your own database.

Step 4: Run the Website

Here's the part a lot of people get stuck on — you cannot just double-click index.html and expect it to work. This project uses JavaScript modules, and browsers block those when you open a file directly. You need to run it through a simple local server instead.
Easiest way — using VS Code:

Open the project folder in VS Code
Install the Live Server extension (search for it in the Extensions tab)
Right-click on index.html → "Open with Live Server"
Your browser will open the site automatically

If you don't want to use VS Code:
bashpython -m http.server 5500
Then open http://localhost:5500 in your browser.

Step 5: Check If It's Working

Go to the Report Lost or Report Found page and submit a test item
Open your Firebase Console → Firestore Database — you should see your test item appear there instantly
Go to the Browse page — your test item should show up there too